com.joliciel.talismane.lexicon

Interface WritableLexicalEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    LexicalEntry, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompactLexicalEntry

    public interface WritableLexicalEntry
extends LexicalEntry
    A writable lexical entry. When adding a value, the resulting List is guaranteed to be in ascending order.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli

      • setAttribute

        void setAttribute(java.lang.String attribute,
                  java.lang.String value)
        If the attribute is a LexicalEntry, it will set the corresponding entry. If not, it will associate the next available OtherAttribute with the attribute name provided, and store the value against this attribute. If all eight OtherAttributes are already taken, an Exception should be thrown.
